DataType.Name: Auto_Req
DataType.Comment: Request to put the uncoiler in automatic mode.

DataType.Name: Manual_Req
DataType.Comment: Request to put the uncoiler in manual mode.

DataType.Name: Auto_Feedback
DataType.Comment: Feedback that the uncoiler is in auto mode.

DataType.Name: Manual_Feedback
DataType.Comment: Feedback that the uncoiler is in manual mode.

DataType.Name: TargetVariable
DataType.Comment: Present values of variables with the Retain attribute Transfer Flag

DataType.Name: TargetMemory
DataType.Comment: Present values of memory used for CJ-series Units with the Retain attribute Transfer Flag

DataType.Name: Num
DataType.Comment: Command Pulse Count Per Motor Rotation

DataType.Name: Den
DataType.Comment: Work Travel Distance Per Motor Rotation

DataType.Name: Feed_Complete_Time
DataType.Comment: Pulse time when the feed is complete. Standalone feeder option.

DataType.Name: Reset_Sequence
DataType.Comment: Resets the whole sequence on rising edge.

DataType.Name: Entry_Feed_Micro_Feedback
DataType.Comment: Feedback that the feeder is actually in micro mode.

DataType.Name: Exit_Feed_Micro_Feedback
DataType.Comment: Feedback that the feeder is actually in micro mode.

DataType.Name: Start_Feed
DataType.Comment: Button to start the feeding sequence

DataType.Name: Reset_Feed_Counter
DataType.Comment: Button to reset the standalone feeding counter.

DataType.Name: Recipe_Transfered
DataType.Comment: A new recipe has been transfered from the HMI. Reset the sequence step number and number of sequences. Give a delay for gag activation.

DataType.Name: Gag_Fault_Msg
DataType.Comment: Gag_Numbers of what has not activated or deactivated properly.

DataType.Name: HMI_Transfer_Msg
DataType.Comment: Message representing the state of the feeder.

DataType.Name: Feed_Counter_Alarm
DataType.Comment: Standalone feeder counter has been reached.

DataType.Name: Home_Entry_Feeder
DataType.Comment: Trigger to home the entry feeder.

DataType.Name: Last_Recorded_Value
DataType.Comment: Last recorded value using the recoding function.

DataType.Name: Current_Recording
DataType.Comment: Current jog distance (reset each time a new jog move is started)

DataType.Name: Feed_Sig_Lost
DataType.Comment: Active when the Press comes out of the feeding angles, but the feeder is still feeding.

DataType.Name: Release
DataType.Comment: If we receive a feeding signal while waiting for the release signal or releasing from the feeder then give an alarm

DataType.Name: Uncoiler_Not_Auto
DataType.Comment: Uncoiler must be in auto to start the feeder.

DataType.Name: Gag
DataType.Comment: A gag was not activated, or deactivated, in the correct timeframe.

DataType.Name: Entry_Deviation
DataType.Comment: Entry feeder has deviated too far from its respective feed distance.

DataType.Name: Exit_Deviation
DataType.Comment: Exit feeder has deviated too far from its respective feed distance.

DataType.Name: Main_Deviation
DataType.Comment: Main feeder has deviated too far from its respective feed distance.

DataType.Name: Gag_Forced
DataType.Comment: A gag is forced, unforce gag to start in auto.

DataType.Name: Press_Mtr_Not_Started
DataType.Comment: Start the motor of the press before feedintg in auto.

DataType.Name: Feed_Release
DataType.Comment: Releasing while feeding. Preventive alarm found in press countroller when integrated with feeder.

DataType.Name: Entry_Max_Torque
DataType.Comment: Entry feeder has torqued too much.

DataType.Name: Exit_Max_Torque
DataType.Comment: Exit feeder has torqued too much.

DataType.Name: Main_Max_Torque
DataType.Comment: Main feeder has torqued too much.

DataType.Name: Recipe_Loading
DataType.Comment: Load a recipe before putting the feeder in auto.

DataType.Name: Feeders_Clamp
DataType.Comment: Both feeders are clamped - cannot feed.

DataType.Name: Alternating_Distance
DataType.Comment: Distance at which we alternate between the two feeders.

DataType.Name: Bypass_Encoder_Alarm_Entry
DataType.Comment: Bypass encoder alarms. Will still be seen on screen but won't stop the feeder.

DataType.Name: Bypass_Encoder_Alarm_Exit
DataType.Comment: Bypass encoder alarms. Will still be seen on screen but won't stop the feeder.

DataType.Name: Bypass_Encoder_Alarm_Main
DataType.Comment: Bypass encoder alarms. Will still be seen on screen but won't stop the feeder.

DataType.Name: Manual_Speed_Limit
DataType.Comment: Maximum speed in manual mode. Metric ONLY!!!!!

DataType.Name: Manual_Speed_Limit_Micro
DataType.Comment: Maximum speed in manual micro mode. Metric ONLY!!!!

DataType.Name: Straightner_Enc_Raw_Max
DataType.Comment: Value representing the maximum in raw encoder pulses.
